NEWS PAGE — REBUILD PROMPT
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════


PROJECT CONTEXT

    Part of the NALA locksmith website.
    Stack: Bootstrap 5, jQuery, Material Icons, Font Awesome.
    wc.subscribe / wc.publish = pub/sub via PubSub.js
    wc.log = dev console logger
    Branch: 04.20.2026 at https://github.com/NYCMEL/nala-website


DIRECTORY

    news/
        index.inc.html      ← main page file (wc-include fragment)
        news.js             ← renders cards + article detail view
        news.config.js      ← article data (window.NEWS_CONFIG)
        news.scss           ← all styles (NEVER edit news.css directly)


PAGE LAYOUT

    Row 1 — full-width video row (grid-column: 1 / -1):
        3 Vimeo videos side by side, each in its own .news-video-item
        Use full embed URLs with app_id=58479 (required by Vimeo security)

    Row 2 — 3 equal article columns:
        Cards distributed from hidden #newsGrid into #newsGridCol2/3/4
        Distribution is done via JS after news.js fires news:grid-rendered

    Container: .container (Bootstrap), max-width 1200px, centered
    Grid: .news-three-col → repeat(3, 1fr), gap: 10px both axes
    Column gap between cards: 10px (flex column + gap:10px on .news-col-articles)


VIDEO EMBED URLS (use exactly — app_id required)

    Safe Lockout:
        https://player.vimeo.com/video/1106503990?title=0&byline=0&portrait=0&badge=0&autopause=0&player_id=0&app_id=58479

    Marketing Video 3.2:
        https://player.vimeo.com/video/1106503753?title=0&byline=0&portrait=0&badge=0&autopause=0&player_id=0&app_id=58479

    Marketing Video 1.3:
        https://player.vimeo.com/video/1106503213?title=0&byline=0&portrait=0&badge=0&autopause=0&player_id=0&app_id=58479

    Vimeo player API script:
        <script src="https://player.vimeo.com/api/player.js"></script>

    Video wrapper: 16:9 ratio via padding-top:56.25% + position:relative
    Label bar: dark (#111) background, gray (#adb5bd) text, 11px, centered


CARD DIMENSIONS

    .news-card:
        height: 380px
        width: 100%
        margin-bottom: 10px

    .news-card__image (header band):
        height: 72px (fixed, original size — do NOT override)
        gold gradient background

    .news-card__body:
        flex: 1
        overflow: hidden
        excerpt area: overflow-y:auto, min-height:0, flex:1

    .news-card__meta (date + Read More):
        flex-shrink: 0 — always visible at bottom, never clipped


ARTICLE DISTRIBUTION (JS)

    news.js renders all cards into a hidden #newsGrid div (position:absolute,
    visibility:hidden, height:0, overflow:hidden) inside .news-page.

    A distribution script subscribes to 'news:grid-rendered' (fired by news.js
    after it populates #newsGrid), then:
        1. Selects all .news-card elements from #newsGrid
        2. Clones each card (cloneNode(true))
        3. Distributes clones round-robin across #newsGridCol2, #newsGridCol3,
           #newsGridCol4 using index % 3
        4. Re-binds .news-card__link click on each clone:
               → dispatches a MouseEvent('click') on the original hidden link
               → news.js handles article detail view from there

    Fallback: setTimeout(distributeArticles, 1000) in case wc isn't ready.

    Poll loop: if wc.subscribe isn't available yet, poll every 100ms until it is.


NEWS.JS PATCHES (applied — keep these)

    showArticle() saves/restores page.innerHTML (not just container.innerHTML)
    so the 3-column layout + videos are correctly restored on Back button.

    showGrid() re-publishes 'news:grid-rendered' after restore so the
    distribution script re-runs and clones are re-populated.

    Container selector updated to: page.querySelector('.container-fluid, .container')

    Article detail view replaces page.innerHTML with a clean single-column
    layout (max-width:800px, centered) including the Back button, article
    header, and body. CSS link is re-injected inline.


NEWS.SCSS (canonical — always use this as base)

    @import "../css/nala.scss";

    .news-page     — padding 20px 0 40px, bg $color-bg-light, min-height calc
    .news-header   — centered, border-bottom 2px #a98211, margin-bottom 20px
    .news-title    — 32px, 700 weight
    .news-subtitle — 16px, secondary color

    .news-grid     — grid repeat(3,1fr), gap 24px (used only by hidden #newsGrid,
                     not the visible columns — visible columns use flex)

    .news-card     — white bg, 12px radius, flex column, height:380px, width:100%,
                     margin-bottom:10px, border 1px #e8eaed, box-shadow

    .news-card__image   — gradient #a98211→#7a5e0c, height:72px
    .news-card__body    — padding 20px, flex column, flex:1, overflow:hidden
    .news-card__excerpt — flex:1, overflow-y:auto, min-height:0
    .news-card__meta    — flex-shrink:0, border-top 1px #f0f0f0, margin-top:auto
    .news-card__link    — color #a98211, 13px, 600 weight

    .news-article  — white bg, 12px radius, padding 32px 40px 40px, border
    .news-article__back — gold border button, hover fills gold
    .news-article__title — 28px, 700 weight
    .news-article__body p — 16px, line-height 1.8


RESPONSIVE

    Below 767px: grid collapses to 1fr, videos stack vertically


PAGES CONFIG

    Add to mtk-pages.config.js:
        { "cache": "false", "page": "news", "label": "News",
          "url": "<wc-include href='news/index.inc.html' />" }

    Add nav link in header to publish 'news' or navigate to #news.


CRITICAL RULES

    1. NEVER edit news.css directly — always edit news.scss
    2. Videos require full embed URL with app_id=58479
    3. Cards are CLONED from hidden #newsGrid — never moved (appendChild moves DOM nodes)
    4. news.js saves/restores full page.innerHTML — not just the container
    5. wc.publish('news:grid-rendered') must be called after grid restore so
       distribution re-runs
    6. .news-card__meta must always have flex-shrink:0 so date/Read More never disappear
